.TH CWE-125 7 "2026-06-22" "CWE Top 25 (2025)" "Software Weakness Reference"
.SH NAME
CWE\-125 \- Out\-of\-bounds Read
.SH RANK
2025 CWE Top 25 rank: \fB#8\fR (2024 rank: 6).
.SH CLASSIFICATION
Class: Memory Safety.
.SH DESCRIPTION
Data is read past the end (or before the start) of a buffer, leaking adjacent memory (keys, pointers, other data) or crashing. Often arises from trusting a length or index from untrusted input. A C/C++ class; managed runtimes bounds\-check.
.SH MITIGATION
Validate every index and length against the actual buffer size before reading; use correct loop bounds. In C++ prefer .at() and range\-based iteration. Sanitizers and fuzzing find many of these.
.SH KNOWN EXPLOITED VULNERABILITIES
CISA KEV catalog (as of 2026-06-22): \fB17\fR exploited CVEs mapped to this weakness.
.PP
CVE\-2014\-0160, CVE\-2016\-5198, CVE\-2017\-5030, CVE\-2020\-11899, CVE\-2021\-25487, CVE\-2022\-22674, CVE\-2022\-22675, CVE\-2023\-28204, CVE\-2023\-36424, CVE\-2023\-42916, CVE\-2024\-53150, CVE\-2025\-5419, CVE\-2025\-5777, CVE\-2025\-22226, CVE\-2025\-24991, CVE\-2026\-3055, CVE\-2026\-11645.
.SH EXAMPLES
One vulnerable\->fixed pair per ecosystem (C, C++).
.SS C
\fIVulnerable:\fR
.RS
.EX
int sum_n(const int *a, size_t len, size_t n) {
    int s = 0;
    for (size_t i = 0; i <= n; i++)   /* '<=' and unchecked n read past end */
        s += a[i];
    return s;
}
.EE
.RE
\fIFixed:\fR
.RS
.EX
int sum_n(const int *a, size_t len, size_t n) {
    int s = 0;
    size_t limit = (n < len) ? n : len;   /* clamp to the buffer */
    for (size_t i = 0; i < limit; i++)
        s += a[i];
    return s;
}
.EE
.RE
.SS C++
\fIVulnerable:\fR
.RS
.EX
int v = vec[i];     // operator[] does no bounds check; i may be out of range
.EE
.RE
\fIFixed:\fR
.RS
.EX
int v = vec.at(i);  // bounds-checked: throws std::out_of_range instead
.EE
.RE
